<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1436,151,800]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,739,764]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Distribution.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Uvarov" box="[524,694,739,763]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Uvarov, B. P. (1934) Entomological Expedition to Abyssinia, 1926 - 7: Orthoptera of the families Mantidae, Gryllidae, Tettigoniidae, and Acrididae. Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 38, 591 - 614. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1934. tb 00998. x" type="journal article" year="1934">Uvarov (1934)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Ragge" box="[756,913,739,764]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Ragge, D. R. (1980) A review of the African Phaneropterinae with open tympana (Orthoptera: Tettigoniidae). Bulletin of the British Museum (Natural History) Entomology, 40, 1 - 192." type="journal article" year="1980">Ragge (1980)</bibRefCitation>
the distribution of this species extends from Shewa province down to the region of 
<collectingRegion box="[585,641,775,800]" country="South Sudan" name="Lakes" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Lake</collectingRegion>
Abaya in the extreme north of Sidamo province.
</paragraph>
